  "texts": [
    "The Bloch waves |p, lσ⟩ and |p + G l G, lσ⟩ are not independent and only differ up to a phase.",
    "In other words, k is a crystal momentum.",
    "For simplicity, we therefore always pick the representative whose momentum label lies closest to K l. The locality of the hopping derives from the fact that we neglected the p dependence in the hopping amplitude in the last line of Eq. 126.",
    "Retaining the momentum-dependence leads to corrections known as non-local tunneling or momentum-dependent tunneling."
